  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Implemention of the Citizenship Training Model in Education Establishments and Secretariats, as a Strategy of Education for Peace - Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of the National Training Plan for Citizenship that seeks to strengthen the education sector in the development of strategies that contribute to the construction of peace and the transformation of the school into a space for the development and practice of citizenship competencies for the exercise of human rights. In this sense, the project seeks to contribute to the implementation of the Training Model for Citizenship in educational establishments and focalized Education Secretariats, through the development of pedagogical strategies and social mobilization that strengthen the citizenship and socio-emotional competencies of teachers and managers of the prioritized educational establishments, and of the officials of the Secretariats of Education; and promote the inclusive and intercultural education of the targeted ethnic groups. The Training Model for Citizenship of the Ministry of Education has integrated the development of basic skills for the guarantee of the rights of ethnic groups and the recognition of an intercultural rights and citizenship approach for differential attention.</narrative>
  </description>
